OL,3,CBank of England cuts interest rates
OL,4,Cfor second time this year
OL,6,FRates had been sitting at 5% after
OL,7,Fbeing cut by 0.25 percentage points in
OL,8,FAugust, the first reduction since
OL,9,F2020, before Bank of England committee
OL,10,Fmembers voted to keep them the same in
OL,11,FSeptember.
OL,13,FThe cut follows official data showing
OL,14,Fthe UK Consumer Prices Index (CPI)
OL,15,Finflation fell to 1.7% in September,
OL,16,Fthe lowest level since April 2021.
OL,18,FThe slowdown, from 2.2% in August, was
OL,19,Fdriven by a sharp slump in petrol
OL,20,Fprices and lower airfares.
